EXTRACTED VALUE: David West will miss Friday's game against the Knicks with a stomach virus.
The Celtics still aren't sure if Marquis Daniels (personal) will be ready to play on Wednesday.
Paul Pierce went 10-of-16 from the field and 4-of-4 from the line to score 25 points in Thursday's win over the Heat.
Aaron Gray played 20 minutes off the Hornets bench on Saturday, posting seven points, 11 rebounds and two blocks.
Emeka Okafor, who didn't attempt a shot in his first game, had 13 points, eight rebounds and four blocks on Friday.
Matt Bonner returned from a back injury but missed all six of his shots, failing to score in 17 minutes.
Celtics selected Notre Dame PF Luke Harangody with the No. 52 pick in the draft.
Ime Udoka was active for Wednesday night's game against the Raptors but was a healthy scratch from the lineup.

36-year-old veteran Antonio McDyess will likely be forced to play a bigger role than usual for the Spurs' injury-depleted frontcourt.
Tony Parker hit just 4-of-12 shots for nine points, four rebounds, one assist and four turnovers in Friday's loss to the Mavericks.
Celtics rookie Avery Bradley continues to rehab his surgically-repaired ankle.
The Mavericks will not re-sign Von Wafer -- his 10-day contract expired following Friday's game.
George Hill left Monday's game in the fourth quarter due to cramps in his right calf.
Ray Allen drained five three-pointers on his way to 20 points in Tuesday's season opener against the Heat. He was 7-of-13 from the field.
Glen Davis has drawn a team-high 19 charges this season. The only other Celtic to have taken multiple charges is Jermaine O'Neal (2).
Free agent C D.J. Mbenga worked out for the Blazers on Monday.
David Anderson (back) returned to action on Wednesday, scoring nine points on 2-of-4 shooting with four rebounds and no assists in 17 minutes.
Richard Jefferson scored eight points on 2-of-7 shooting (including two threes) with four rebounds, one steal, and one block on Monday.
Pops Mensa-Bonsu has accepted an invitation to Hornets training camp.
Shaquille O'Neal is on the team plane to Cleveland after missing Monday's practice.
Marco Belinelli played just 22 minutes in Monday's game, scoring eight points on 2-of-5 shooting with one rebound and no assists.
Rajon Rondo (knee, hamstring, foot) and Shaquille O'Neal (knee) are both questionable for Wednesday's game against the Nuggets.

Marcus Thornton (right quad) is probable for Friday's game at Portland.
Manu Ginobili had 26 points, six rebounds, six assists, two steals, a block and four 3-pointers in a comeback, overtime win against the Timberwolves.

Jermaine O'Neal (knee) is hoping to resume working out next week.

Semih Erden contributed nine points and four rebounds in 13 minutes off the bench on Sunday.
Jarrett Jack, David Andersen and Marcus Banks are expected to join the Hornets in L.A. on Monday for a game against the Clippers.
Spurs rookie James Anderson (hamstring) is almost ready to resume full basketball activities.
Spurs coach Gregg Popovich said that Tiago Splitter will play when he plays, coming after two straight DNP-CDs.
